Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says South Africans will be able to go for a run or walk their dogs during the Coronavirus lockdown. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says South Africans will be able to go for a run or walk their dogs during the COVID-19 lockdown. The country is gearing up for spending 21 days at home from Friday. READ: COVID-19 cases in SA climb to 709 You'll only be allowed to leave your home under exceptional circumstances, like buying food. Mkhize says you will, however, be allowed to get out for some fresh air.